definition.value: Serous sac, which has as parts a synovial membrane and a synovial cavity. Examples: synovial bursa, synovial tendon sheath of index finger, synovial capsule of knee joint.

Body cavity subdivision which is surrounded by the internal surface of the right or left side of the rib cage, the right or left lateral surface of the mediastinum and the superior surface of a hemidiaphragm. Examples: There are only two canonical instances, cavity of right hemithorax and cavity of left hemithorax.

Somatic cell which has as its part a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.  It may either contain keratin, vimentin or vimentin-like intermediate filaments.
